Setup Instructions
==================
Install and Compile GLFW and GLAD for your OS. Then, follow the steps
below to configure your project in an IDE to use these necessary files.

C++ Files
---------
- Add glfw/include as an additional include directory
- Add glad/include as an additional include directory
- Add gl.c as an external source file, which should be in glad/src

Linking
-------
- As an additional library directories add the library folder in glfw
  matching your version of Visual Studio.
- In input, add the following as additional dependencies:
  + glfwX.lib, where X is your version of glfw (for example, glfw3.dll)
  + opengl32.lib
  + user32.lib
  + gdi32.lib
  + shell32.lib